  "text": "Let us consider the spherical wave in high loss medium. In order to detect such a wave we use a dielectric ball in high loss medium where the eigen oscillations formed by spherical waves are excited. The complex permittivity of a ball and an outer medium are ε 1 and ε 2 , respectively. We consider a quasioptical case, when the ball radius is a λ (λ is an operating wave length). The characteristic equations for eigen oscillations in the ball are presented earlier in [CITATION_1] .",
